⍝ APL (A Programming Language) - Lorentz Factor Simulation
⍝ --------------------------------------------------------
⍝ This script calculates the Lorentz factor (γ) of a proton 
⍝ inside the Large Hadron Collider at its maximum velocity.
⍝ 
⍝ APL is chosen for its highly exotic, alien-like syntax 
⍝ which perfectly aligns with the extreme mathematics of CERN.

⍝ Velocity of proton at LHC (v) as a fraction of c (speed of light)
v ← 0.999999991

⍝ Lorentz factor formula: γ = 1 / √(1 - v²)
γ ← ÷ *∘0.5 1 - v*2

⍝ Display the esoteric mathematical payload
⎕ ← '--- CERN LHC KINETIC DIAGNOSTICS ---'
⎕ ← 'Proton Velocity (v/c): ', ⍕v
⎕ ← 'Lorentz Factor (γ): ', ⍕γ
⎕ ← 'Status: MAXIMUM ENERGY ATTAINED'
